# Formatting Rule for Blog Posts

When writing or editing blog posts, follow these capitalization rules for headings:
- **H1 (Title)**: Always Title Case
- **H2**: Always Sentence case
- **H3**: Title Case

**Exception**: Always capitalize proper nouns, regardless of the heading level or case rule.

# Design System Rules

Before writing or modifying any UI code, read the relevant
spec file in `specs/`. Use only tokens from `src/app/tokens.css`.
Run `node scripts/token-audit.js` before committing. Zero errors required.

Key references:
- **Token definitions:** `src/app/tokens.css` (three-layer architecture)
- **Foundation specs:** `specs/foundations/` (color, spacing, typography, radius, elevation, motion)
- **Component specs:** `specs/components/` (anatomy, tokens, states, examples)
- **Token master map:** `specs/tokens/token-reference.md`

Rules:
1. Never use hardcoded hex/rgba colors, px spacing, raw font-sizes,
   font-weights, box-shadows, or z-index values in CSS or `sx` props.
2. Reference `var(--token-name)` from tokens.css for all visual values.
3. In MUI `sx` props, keep MUI palette refs (`"primary.main"`, `"text.secondary"`)
   where they map correctly to the design system. Only use `var()` for values
   that MUI doesn't cover (raw shadows, on-dark colors, custom transitions).
4. For Framer Motion, reference the numeric equivalents documented in
   `specs/foundations/motion.md`.
